        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-09 12:12:33.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n@MilanVerespej I have two reasons to keep it separate:\n1. Previous commit was cleaner and looked nicer to me and I want to have it it in git history - otherwise it would be lost, this commit looks IMHO uglier but it is unnecessary to add more features - but because of the issues the following commits bring to the installer we can decide to abondon the effort, but the first commit can still be applied without affecting the rest of the playbook.\n\n2. It is completely fine workflow to work on a branch and make a Pull Request to which other subsequent commits can be pushed (github workflow for example) and it makes hell of a more sense to me - this commit is not fixing a bug or adding a commentary. It rewrites the usage and flow of the module.\n\nIs it somewhere explicitly written that this project does not allow such a workflow? Maybe it is, I dunno.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
